&lt;p&gt;27 Hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen in the North East Derbyshire 0-19 team for a Band 6 SCPHN School Nurse, to be based primarily in Dronfield.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a SCPHN School Nurse looking to work in an innovative supportive trust then DCHS is for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;North East Derbyshire locality covers the eastern side of the north of the County. We have a new contract which enables us to use our Public Health skills to address public health outcomes for the young people in North East Derbyshire locality and are looking for a motivated enthusiastic SCPHN to join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DCHS is an inclusive employer who take the well being of their staff seriously. On joining us you would be supported to access excellent training both mandatory and role specific, an induction programme and both clinical and safeguarding supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So if you are passionate about making a difference to the lives of young people whilst working for a great employer in a supportive team of talented nurses whilst driving around one of the most beautiful parts of the world then come and see us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Take a look at our trust values and if you have these values and want to be part of a team that embraces these then come and see us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alison Tranter 07837 061633&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;alison.tranter@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
